children.description:
Create a radial gradient. To add colors, use the `addColorStop` method on the returned Gradient, like this:

> gradient.addColorStop(0, 'black');
> gradient.addColorStop(0.5, '#2222FF');
> gradient.addColorStop(1, 'rgba(0,0,0,0');

 The first argument is the place of the stop: `0` is the starting point, `1` is the end. The second argument is the color at that stop; any CSS-compatible color is allowed.

> __Note:__ Use a gradient as a value for strokeStyle or fillStyle.

